        <front/>
        <body>
            <pb n="1" facs="#f0001"/>
            <lb break="yes"/>
            <div n="1">
                <head>
                    <hi rendition="#i">Extent and Population of America.</hi>
                </head>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>The following estimate of the extent in<lb break="yes"/>square leagues and in
                    population, of the<lb break="yes"/>continent of America, in 1822, was late-<lb
                        break="no"/>ly transmitted by the Baron de Humboldt,<lb break="yes"/>from
                    Paris, to president Bolivar with the<lb break="yes"/>accompanying letter:<space
                        dim="horizontal"/>[<hi rendition="#i">Niles&#x2019; Reg.</hi>
                </p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <table>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#i">Square<lb break="yes"/>Leagues.</hi></cell>
                        <cell> <hi rendition="#i">Popula-<lb break="no"/>tion.</hi></cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Mexico, or New Spain</cell>
                        <cell>75,830</cell>
                        <cell>6,800,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Guatemala</cell>
                        <cell>16,740</cell>
                        <cell>1,600,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Cuba and Puerto Rico</cell>
                        <cell>4,430</cell>
                        <cell>800,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell rows="3">Colombia <list rendition="#leftBraced">
                            <item>Venezuela</item>
                            <item>New Granada</item>
                        </list></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>33,700</cell>
                        <cell>900,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>58,250</cell>
                        <cell>1,800,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row><cell/></row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Peru</cell>
                        <cell>42,150</cell>
                        <cell>1,400,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Chili</cell>
                        <cell>14,240</cell>
                        <cell>1,100,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Buenos Ayres</cell>
                        <cell>126,770</cell>
                        <cell>2,000,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>_____________</cell>
                        <cell>_____________</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Total, formerly Spanish,</cell>
                        <cell>372,110</cell>
                        <cell>16,400,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>   United States</cell>
                        <cell><choice><sic>125,44</sic><corr type="editorial">125,440</corr></choice></cell>
                        <cell>10,200,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>   Brazil</cell>
                        <cell>256,990</cell>
                        <cell>4,000,000</cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                
                <p>The above surfaces have been calculat-<lb break="no"/>ed with great care, on maps
                    rectified by<lb break="yes"/>astronomical observations. These calcu-<lb
                        break="no"/>lations have been several times repeated<lb break="yes"/>by M
                    Mathieu, member of the board of<lb break="yes"/>longitude and of the institute,
                    as well as<lb break="yes"/>myself The results differ from those<lb break="yes"
                    />published in <choice>
                        <sic>1800</sic>
                        <corr type="editorial">1809</corr>
                    </choice>, in the political essay<lb break="yes"/>on Mexico. Then the inhabited
                        parts<lb break="yes"/>alone had been calculated, without includ-<lb
                        break="no"/>ing the desert regions, over which the<lb break="yes"
                    />independent tribes of the indigenous in-<lb break="no"/>habitants wander. Now
                    the whole extent<lb break="yes"/>of each country, to its farthest limits, has<lb
                        break="yes"/>been measured.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>The population of the different parts of<lb break="yes"/><choice>
                        <sic><hi rendition="#i">cidevant</hi></sic>
                        <corr type="editorial"><hi rendition="#i">ci-devant</hi></corr>
                    </choice> Spanish America is uncertain;<lb break="yes"/>nevertheless, each
                    proportion has been<lb break="yes"/>calculated according to the latest data<lb
                        break="yes"/>which have reached me. The present<lb break="yes"/>estimate
                    ought to be considered in the<lb break="yes"/>same light as all my other works
                    on A-<lb break="no"/>merica; they are no other than essays, in<lb break="yes"
                    />which every thing will have to be done<lb break="yes"/>over again. Statistical
                    calculations can<lb break="yes"/>only be rendered perfect by degrees, in<lb
                        break="yes"/>like manner as the elements of meteoro-<lb break="no"/>logical
                    and astronomical tables.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>
                    <hi rendition="#i">Comparison.</hi>&#x2014;Spain contains 16,094<lb break="yes"
                    />square leagues&#x2014;Europe contains 304,710<lb break="yes"/>square leagues,
                    and the whole of South-<lb break="no"/>ern America 581,891 square leagues.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        <hi rendition="#et">(Signed) HUMBOLDT.</hi>
                    </salute>
                </closer>
            </div>
